com.gh.bmd.jrt.android.builder

Interface InvocationServiceRoutineBuilder<INPUT,OUTPUT>

  • Type Parameters:
    INPUT - the input data type.
    OUTPUT - the output data type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    ConfigurableBuilder, Routine<INPUT,OUTPUT>, RoutineBuilder<INPUT,OUTPUT>, ServiceRoutineBuilder

    public interface InvocationServiceRoutineBuilder<INPUT,OUTPUT>
extends ServiceRoutineBuilder, RoutineBuilder<INPUT,OUTPUT>
    Interface defining a builder of routine objects based on an invocation class token.
    The invocation execution will happen in a dedicated service.

    The local context of the invocations will be the specific service instance.

    Created by davide on 3/7/15.

      • withArgs

        @Nonnull
InvocationServiceRoutineBuilder<INPUT,OUTPUT> withArgs(@Nullable
                                                             Object... args)
        Sets the arguments to be passed to the invocation constructor.

        Note that, like the object passed to the service routine input and output channels, the specified arguments must comply with the Parcel.writeValue(Object) method. Be aware though, that issues may arise when employing Serializable objects on the Lollipop OS version, so, it is advisable to use Parcelable objects instead.

        Parameters:
        args - the arguments.
        Returns:
        this builder.
